text:
✨
.
.
.
#fearless
.
.
i’ve been working on something recently that has been mentally, emotionally and spiritually draining. it’s been a process of facing fear. then waking up and doing it again. i have to speak about it in general terms with some people, and  break down about it with trusted close friends. keeping it so private has been hard.
.
.
this process is a daily reminder for me that i have no idea what your struggle is. what the person at the bank, or driving in front of me 😬, or sitting on the street corner is going through, or has been through. with all my heart i believe that the toughest things when faced head on can soften us to connect more deeply with people. be it intimately, or in passing acknowledgment of each other’s humanness.
.
and that’s what it’s all about #relationships .
.
so whatever you are going through today, be it public or very private, i see you. and you are loved. 💙
.
.
#facingfears is #courageous

text:
some of montréal artist françoise sullivan’s gorgeous sculptural pieces from the 1960s. 
i  had never heard of sullivan before seeing this show, and i don’t think i’m alone, even though she was central to montréal’s burgeoning art scene in the 40s and 50s, and a signatory of quebec’s anti-establishment and anti-religion refus global manifesto that made so many other artists (all men) famous, esp. jean-paul riopelle and paul-émile borduas. nice to see her work getting the limelight in the #metoo era

text:
today i did something i never thought i would have the courage to do. today marks 2 years since my parents received the most horrific call of their life. the call that would shake any parent when you answer at 2am in the morning hearing your daughter screaming & choking on her own tears.

today was the day that changed my entire life. today is the date i was sexually assaulted. 
today is the day i am sharing my journey of what it took to heal & becoming #becomingramirez.

i drove to the gas station ⛽️ that i stumbled into after i was assaulted and asked to speak with the indian man who helped me through the door.
cleaned up my wounds.
covered me with anything he could place over my half dressed body.
grabbed napkins to dry the blood and gave me water.

i never revisited the gas station nor the scene of it all because it was too traumatizing but today i did 🙏🏽 ✨i wanted to thank him because he was the one to call 911 & he saved my life! ✨
_
_
_
to the indian man who rescued me that night when all i wanted to do was run home to my parents & keep all of this a secret.... thank you for calling 😭✨ because of you
i was healing right then and there with your counsel & your compassion!

the simple act of him making that call 
allowed me to get a year of therapy, support group & justice from the city’s police department... all because of his call & description of me!
-
-
-
although i could not locate you sir, 2 years later on this very day. thank you so much!
-
-
-
full day of my healing is in my instastories if you wish to see what i was able to do. the wee bit of courage i had in me before i completely broke down crying to my girlfriend @isabelsth  in front of the gas station.

this is healing from sexual trauma! 
this is #becomingramirez .
.
.
.
.
#dezramirez #desiraeramirez #metoo #timesup #whywewearblack #sexualassaultsurvivor #healing #vulnerabilityisstrength #breakthesilence #believesurvivors #believewoman #erasethehate #yourvoicematters #yourhealingmatters #bravery #couragetochange #kindnessiseverything

😤😡 #repost @monachalabi 
felipe gómez alonzo died on christmas eve while in the "care" of us immigration officials. he was 8 years old. he died less than 3 weeks after 7 year-old jakelin caal maquin, drawn here.

at times i forget just how dire this ongoing situation is. but children depend on adults not forgetting them. there are approximately 15,000 children right now in federally contracted shelters. that number has risen from 12,800 in september. (i drew this graphic last week for @guardian_us). if you can, donate to @raicestexas which provides free and low-cost legal services to underserved immigrants or @aclu_nationwide or, especially if you're spanish speaking, volunteer. it's so much more meaningful than an instagram like. 
source: new york times estimates based on information reported to members of congress, december 2018.

text:
and for the last few months of reflection: september to november 🍁— the leaves were changing...as was the pace of life!
.
.
.
that woman i’m sitting next to, is a hidden figure. the 
@washingtonianmag published article on sandra bundy. she’s the woman at the heart of the first case that made sexual harassment a legal concept in america. yet, even with #metoo movements and #timesup...you probably haven’t heard her name. well, @ciara_leone365 aaron and i spent a few hours with her...and well — i’m hoping you’ll get to see that piece, and hear her story, very soon.
.
.
.

speaking of #blackwomen...made my way over to baltimore for an incredible event curated by @denise.om.shanti — design for the well-being of black women. powerful space. also finally hosted a long-awaited clothing swap and discussion on fast fashion and sustainability. i will say, pursuing #sustainability practices (zero waste, equitable/eco-friendly food, clothing, etc.) is tough to maintain while on the road! so, i’m looking forward to learning more about implementing those practices in travel in 2019. .
.
.
by october, started getting used to the ny skyline. also experienced a whole lotta burroughs.  you may remember i also got locked into a spot in brooklyn? good times, good times. .
.
.
in november, after four long years finally got to spend some soulful time in #uganda. explored new places and markets (pictured), and - most importantly - spent hours interviewing my grandma. felt like some of the most important interviews i’ve done honestly. still haven’t organized all the footage from that trip, to the chagrin of my family...forgive me!
.
.
.
sat down with bernie to talk the “fight for $15” and amazon’s move to raise the minimum wage. .
.
.
let’s not forget, this season was in the heat of the midterms. while on the trail i met dave chappelle who, along with @vanjones68 was campaigning for ben jealous, then-candidate for governor in maryland. long shoot days with sir @_benpalm.
.
.

and well, you probably recognize this by now! we launched a new show! it’s been a real adventure. if you’ve wondered how to watch, visit “nowthis morning” on fb for the fun.

text:
maude girard is a french photographer born in annecy. with a journalistic background she is currently developing several long-term projects on a documentary basis. inspired by a lineage of strong women and by the movement #metoo and its corollaries, she is exploring the concept of femininity. through her first documentary project, pont-marie ou l’appétit du rêve (pont-marie or the appetite for the dream), she witnesses marie’s search and process of identity building as a musician and a millennial woman. wondering about social norms and self-definition obstacles, maude is also questioning her own feminine history through another project called legacy as both a photographer and a granddaughter. she will be presenting her recent ongoing photographic bodies of work evoking her evolving approach and the impact of #metoo on those projects.

#maudegirard #photography #metoo #metoomovement #documentingmetoo #documentaryphotography #conceptualphotography #conceptualartist #artiststranspire #exposingartists #emergingartists #anotherartistemerging

text:
🇬🇧 i thought this lyrics were pretty inspirational. nowadays, we all suffer the social pressure for having a perfect body. i hear almost everyday a comment about how ugly is one of my classmates or how small are someone's tits. i also receive criticism from other girls because "i should wear make up or workout a little bit to flirt more" (even when i am a proud single girl). boys, we are not here to please you! and girls, remember that everytime you say something like that to another girl, you are just supporting the idea that women are just a sexual object. 
ㅤㅤ
🇪🇸 pensé que esta letra era muy inspiradora. hoy en día, todos sufrimos la presión social por tener un cuerpo perfecto. casi todos los días escucho un comentario sobre lo feo que es uno de mis compañeros o lo pequeñas que son las tetas de alguien. también recibo críticas de otras chicas porque "debería usar maquillaje o entrenar un poco para coquetear más" (incluso cuando soy una chica soltera orgullosa). chicos, no estamos aquí para complacerte! y chicas, recuerden que cada vez que le dicen algo así a otra chica, están apoyando la idea de que las mujeres son solo un objeto sexual.

text: i’m leaving the person i was behind. not the person i was before i met you but the person you made me. i was weak, broken, paranoid and terrified. i slept in gym shoes for the first couple months. sleep has never been the same. every time i closed my eyes i saw you. and when i would distract myself for a moment you would force yourself back in my mind. eventually lack of sleep would turn into oversleep. and distractions turned into drugs and alcohol to force out your image.  anything to escape. the thing is that this wasn’t the first time that it’s happened. i was 7years old the first time. 7years old. what you did just brought everything i tried to push away come right back to the surface. but not anymore. i’ve been a prisoner of yours for a long time. can’t smell certain smells, go to certain areas, do anything that reminds me. this painting i made here is me leaving her behind. i didn’t use red paint. i used my blood. i cut my self to feel the pain and as it drips down my finger the pain leaves me too. i used blood because this is the last time i’ll shed blood from you. the last time i will feel pain from you. the last time i will be broken by you. from this point on my pain will be turned to art. i will pour everything into creating. you took so much from me. and now i’m taking it back. this painting is literally a part of me. it was very therapeutic but also took so so much out of me emotionally. i hope you enjoy and please please please share. share because it’s important. share becoi hope to inspire others to turn this pain of sexual assault into something they can’t take away from you. make something beautiful. they’ve taken so much from us. take it right back. we are powerful! we are beautiful and we have been silent for long enough! #metoo #painting #blood #share #metoomovement

text:
our own inner and outer dialogue can be magic or poison. we decide. intentions for 2019.
——————————————
@elizabeth_gilbert_writer “you guys, i can’t do it anymore. i can’t attack myself. i can’t insult myself. i can’t respond to a compliment by offering up a list of my flaws. i just...can’t. it feels like such a violation of the sacred. i don’t have the heart for self-deprecation anymore. somewhere along the way, over the past few years, i’ve lost the dark (and particularly female) talent for self-criticism, and for tearing myself down. it feels like sacrilege. my mouth can’t form the hateful words. and i can’t bear it anymore, to hear another woman demean, degrade, or diminish herself. it shocks my senses and hurts my heart. to witness a woman denying that she is beautiful is like watching someone set fire to an art museum. it’s like watching an angel drink gasoline. it’s like watching a phoenix rip off its wings. i just can’t be around it anymore. it hurts too much. this is my official plea: i beg you to stop doing that. you are a magnificent creature. start knowing it. stop lying about yourself. i love you. onward.” ❤️ lg

•
•

text:
i believe the world (desperately) needs men, but men who are invigorated by a manhood that honors, protects, holds close, and enlivens the world, and everyone in it.
•
the old paradigm of an invulnerable, fearless, stoic masculinity so driven to external success that it can’t hear the cries of the world – or those of his partner, children aching for his loving presence – is outdated.
•
it doesn’t serve anyone anymore, if it ever did.
•
i dare say we need a new model of man, actually.
•
not one that attempts (again) to suit all men, but rather one that encompasses all the magnificent possibilities of what it can mean to be a man.
•
it is my intention that my new podcast - “men, this way” - will serve to illuminate and unleash those possibilities by revealing the massive well of wisdom, the authentic power, the profound love, that lives inside the heart of every human man.
•
episode 1 ~ “there’s no one left to show us …”
•
listen on itunes, stitcher, google play.
•
podcast link in bio
•

das stück wurde während der autor*innentage erstmalig aufgeführt, da die inszenierung hartmanns jedoch so weit vom text entfernt ist, verlangte der fischer verlag vom dt, das wort 'uraufführung' aus dem programm wieder zu streichen. generell frage ich mich, wie man solch eine inszenierung im jahre 2018 überhaupt noch zeigen kann. die protagonistin maria wird fast permanent brutal vergewaltigt, doch wird dieses ästhetisch, mit elektromusik unterlegt, dargestellt. hätte ich es nicht besser gewusst, hätten es auch sexszenen auf der tanzfläche vom kitkatclub sein können, aber keine vergewaltigung. ferner schreit die protagonistin einfach nur wortfetzen. dazu muss man wissen, dass das stück deigners auf einer wahren geschichte einer prostituierten basiert, welche nach jahrzehnten des schweigens dieses endlich bricht. doch hartmann nimmt ihr in seiner inszenierung die sprache wieder. da die aufführung so fern vom text ist, musste das dt diesen auslegen. im text wird die protagonistin nicht permanent vergewaltigt, wie bei hartmann. am ende klagt sie den freund der familie, der sie als kind missbrauchte, an, doch die tat ist verjährt. bei hartmann liegt maria ihm in den armen. im text tauchen noch 3 andere frauen auf. bei hartmann wird die einzige frau auf der bühne permanent extremer sexueller gewalt ausgesetzt. 
am ende hat man mitleid mit der schauspielerin. aber nicht mit maria. 
wie ein theater nach #metoo noch zulassen kann, dass ein regisseur vergewaltigungen durch ästhetische darstellungen verherrlicht, macht mich so unglaublich wütend und ratlos. 
#instanniolpapier #dt #deutschestheaterberlin #deigner

text:
on jan. 1, 2018, more than 300 women in hollywood founded “time’s up,” a global effort to hold sexual abusers accountable. in the year since then, the group ― which includes some of the industry’s most powerful celebrities ― has raised over $20 million and helped thousands of people seek legal recourse.
though activist tarana burke first used “me too” in 2006 as a way to draw attention to the ubiquity of sexual assault and harassment, 2018 supercharged the movement. for many survivors, 2018 was the year their abusers faced consequences: bill cosby was sentenced to prison, harvey weinstein was hit with sex crime charges, and “house of cards” premiered without kevin spacey.
but justice was not unconditional, and many men accused of predatory behavior did just fine in 2018. below is a list of men who continued to thrive despite allegations of misconduct. it is far from exhaustive; it also doesn’t touch on the fact that many accused abusers have been shielded by wealth and generations of white male privilege. louis c.k. is attempting a comedy comeback and matt lauer’s friends have whined to tabloids about how he now has too much free time on his hands.  morgan freeman, ryan seacrest, sylvester stallone, arnold schwarzenegger, nick carter, cristiano ronaldo, roman polanski, r. kelly, james franco, brett kavanaugh & donald trump all still standing ...for now  #metoo
name: Da Minority Report LLC

text: this could be set anywhere because of the absence of names, but it feels so furiously today that it was a slight shock to realise, some way into the pages, that it's modeled after #belfast during the #troubles. the troubles are not central to the story, but the effect political and social divisions have on everyday life is: the hypervigilance of people, the codes of behaviour alien to anyone not in the division, the dogma that resistence itself falls into, the power of rumor and association with those 'beyond the pale'. all brought home through the unwanted attention a powerful man bestows on the 18 year old protagonist and her strategies in responding to him, her maybe-boyfriend, her family and community. i loved it, devoured it, enjoyed the unorthodox style from writing. imagine a long fireside tale, told in stream of consciousness, ebbing and flowing every now and then around ascerbicly funny sentences. #epicwin #milkman #annaburns #bookstagram

text:
resistência: a história de sabrina bittencourt

olá manxs desse brasil! hoje a nossa dr vai ser sobre essa mulher que é uma ativista, que superou arduamente seus traumas, e tornou-se um símbolo de resistência na luta contra o assédio sexual feminino.
.
sabrina de campos bittencourt, teve uma infância marcada por abusos, desde seus 4 anos de idade sofreu violência sexual, por integrantes da igreja que ela frequentava com seus pais (mórmon), aos 16 ficou grávida de um de seus algozes, mas abortou! .
ela diz: “é algo endêmico essa absurda quantidade de líderes de várias religiões que abusam de crianças, jovens e, principalmente, mulheres. desde os quatro anos fui abusada diversas vezes pelos mórmons da igreja que frequentávamos, contra os quais não foi tomada nenhuma providência. o meu caminho foi traçado a partir da dor do outro e da minha dor. eu sabia desde sempre que tinha privilégios que outros não tinham. então, para poder me curar dessas dores, fiz trabalho social intensamente por 20 anos.”
.
quer continuar lendo? acesse nosso site. link na bio!
.
fonte da imagem: divulgação (carta capital)
.

text:
who should pay on the first date? 
i asked this question to a focus group of men, women and teenagers ranging from 16-42. what was fascinating is that, even though there is no hint of gender in the question, the answers are mostly gender based.

it seems silly given if the same gender is dating then who pays? 
the question should be answered from a social perspective e.g. the person doing the inviting and not a gender based one.

text:
- i often speak about removing toxic people from our lives. but sometimes, this is easier said than done. sometimes these people are your mother, your father, a sibling or someone close in your circle. but we still need to ask ourselves, what is the impact of staying around these individuals for a long period of time?  it doesn’t have to be about removing them from your life completely, it’s about limiting the amount of exposure you have to their influential energy. a toxic person is a toxic person no matter the relationship to you.

.

.
.

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

text:
#ringframtidring - ring out the old! ring in the new!  gott nytt år hälsar delar av #tystnadtagning med en önskan om förändring.
.
bakom nyårshälsningen ligger bahar pars och emma broomé och ett hundratal av skådespelerskor, från olika delar av landet, som är medlemmar i #tystnadtagning
.
jag fick äran att vara med på ett hörn i arbetet med pr av denna nyårshälsning. tack till alla i tystnad tagning för ert viktiga arbete och budskap.
"vi vill visa att tillsammans är vi starka och kan åstadkomma en ljusare framtid!"
.
#ringframtidring #ringklockaring #tystnadtagning #metoo #nyårsklockan #bohmbohmroom @baharpars @broomeemma @tystnadtagning.silenceaction svep för att se hela filmen.
name: Emelie Bergbohm

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

✏ jessica thåström

det har varit tungt och lätt på samma gång att läsa denna bok. tungt eftersom det är ett mycket svårt, tungt och för mig ganska oupptäckt ämne med psykisk ohälsa efter ett trauma. lätt eftersom författaren skapat ett driv och en spänning över att följa hennes inre resa efter traumat hon gått igenom. det känns verkligen som att jag får se in i hennes hjärna och hennes inre. hon berättar sin livshistoria så ärligt och öppet att jag blir tårögd flera gånger under läsningen. boken öppnar upp ögonen hos mig och jag lär mig mycket nytt under läsandets gång. jag beundrar jessicas mod och kraft att ta sig igenom och våga berätta om sin psykiska ohälsa och det trauma hon har varit med om. jag är så glad att jag fick läsa din starka berättelse @jessicat.thastrom det är såna som du som inger hopp och visar på att man aldrig ska ge upp kampen om sig själv och sitt eget mående. det känns så konstigt att betygsätta din bok då det känns som att jag då betygsätter ditt liv. din berättelse kommer leva kvar länge hos mig. det blir mitt betyg ❤

die frau als hübsch arrangierte oberfläche: mit diesem klischee spielen die ölgemälde von leonhard hurzlmeier. der 1983 geborene künstler persifliert den männlichen, bewundernden blick auf das weibliche wesen. zusammen mit den bildtiteln erschließt sich sein feinsinniger humor. was ist das überhaupt für ein stil? laut vorwort zu hurzlmeiers bildband neue frauen, der bei hatje cantz erschienen ist, kann man die als vektorgrafiken angelegten motiven der "neo­ pop­ hard­ edge­ figu­ration" zuschreiben. alles klar? wir zeigen eine auswahl. #women #frauen #ölgemälde #art #kunst #leonardhurzlmeier #humor #humour #metoo

text:
surround yourself with healthy resources and establish healthy boundaries. healthy resources could be a loving relationship, nutritious foods, nurturing touch, connections with nature, or a satisfying hobby. a healthy emotional boundary does not accept words or energy directed your way that are not appropriate or healing. *credit: suzanne scurlock-durana from full body presence). here’s one of my healthy resources: my grandma barbara. ❤️❤️
.
the holidays bring us closer to family and inevitably that allows us to have deeper conversations beyond the “likes” and “hearts” of social media. i had a long conversation with my step mom who works with women and children who have fallen victim to or are at risk of domestic violence. maybe it’s just me and my desire to have real conversations with people, instead of superficial small talk about the weather and social activities, that brings me to these deeper conversations.
.
if you’re in a relationship that’s not filling you up, not allowing you to be yourself or you don’t feel safe, get out. no, it’s not easy. yes, you will be scared and go through a period of extreme grief over the loss. yes, help is available. yes, you can do it. you deserve better, regardless of what you’ve been told or what you secretly believe about yourself. you deserve to be treated with respect and honor and love. .
no one, whether it’s a parent, a boyfriend, a girlfriend, a spouse or a friend, have the right to harm you through their words, touch, controlling manipulative behavior, or finances. .
once you’re in a safe place, seek out the healing help you need. you may not have considered physical therapy to be a place to receive the kind of help you need to recover. however, the kind of physical therapy i do is exactly what you need. you won’t be put on a stationary bike or do needless, mindless exercise here. at the healing spot you’ll find the gentle healing touch your body needs to release the pain within. the pain of sexual abuse, verbal abuse, physical abuse, criticism, fear, grief, anxiety. i will hold the healing space you need and i’m just a phone call away 719-270-1123. #womenshealthphysicaltherapy

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
reviewing 2018 and shamelessly tooting my own horn:

1. the 505 boys - as the great @scottjmulligan said "it was the best of times and the worst of times" #lajavanaise
2. turning 21 surrounded by my ucla crew
3. valedictorian of @sciencespo, got my law degree from @univlorraine, ended up on the dean's honors list at @ucla, and reached the 96th percentile on my #lsat
4. in october, the book i've assisted prof. laure murat in writing on the aftermath of #metoo was published in france
5 & 6. i am lucky to have amazing friends around me helping me going through hard times - @lilirochettemonnoury @emma__vinct @senala9 i don't deserve y'all
7. i had the great opportunity to be an intern at the williams institute @uclalawschool. check out their amazing work on lgbt people and rights in the us and all around the world
8. enjoying my last month in la with the best people
9. resting and spending time with family
10. a last goodbye to los angeles and my wonderful #bruins experience

text:
• jbc top ten • number 1️⃣ •

we made it!!! i think a lot of you figured out what my top choice of the year was going to be, but had you told me 6 months ago that my favorite book of 2018 would be the true story of a medical device company manufacturing faulty blood tests, i would have told you to kiss my...”quotient”😂😘. but john carreyrou has managed to write the edge-of-your seat non-fiction thriller of the year. the first half of the book explores the corporate culture of theranos, said medical device company that, at it’s height, was valued at billions of dollars and had enormous contracts with walgreens, safeway and the us military. the latter half of the book charts the collapse of the company and it’s fiery and enigmatic founder, elizabeth holmes.  there’s corporate greed, conspiracy theories, spies, heroes to root for, and plenty of villains to root against. it’s a testament to how great this book is that i ended up buying it on audible just so i could listen to the last 100 pages on the way home from work and ended up sitting in my garage for over an hour finishing this truly bonkers, unbelievable, true story. in a year marked by feminism and the rise of the #metoo movement, it’s hard to decide whether to despise elizabeth holmes for her sociopathic tendencies, or admire and cheer her for managing to really stick it to the man and corporate greed and corruption. regardless, here’s what i can tell you: if you read one of my 2018 book recommendations (and i’ve read over 110 this year), i can say with absolute certainty that bad blood is that book.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
according to a study by ibm and two organizations based out of delhi and their study of wikipedia entries on 4,000 bollywood movies between 1970 and 2017 by ibm and two delhi-based organizations showed that male characters were mentioned nearly twice as many times as their female counterparts. 
sexism was prevalent as female characters are mostly described as “beautiful” and “attractive” whereas men are called “strong” and “successful”. while women go on to marry or love, men were likely to kill or shoot. 
stereotypes or sexist ideas and constructs prevail in the bollywood industry, the item-numbers that shows scantily clad women surrounded by drunk men drooling over her “spicy” or “theeka” body to an upbeat, irrelevant song. 
when the #metoo movement arrived in the industry, it provided many in the industry and the country in whole hope, hope that justice would be served, hope that this massive evil would be erased. but the movement almost like a soda can fizz at first but then almost instantly died out. 
what happened to the movement? why has no action taken place? why did the buck stop at bollywood?
another interesting thought to ponder upon is why did the media houses stop reporting the incidents? did people lose interest? or was the “masala” or the drama just too boring for the public? 
some people believe the movement died down due to the false accusations people were making. to all these people we just have one question to say? have you got to be out of your f*****g mind? 
what next? do we just wait, or are we finally going to speak up about it? something needs to happen, and it needs to happen soon.

according to a study by ibm and two organizations based out of delhi and their study of wikipedia entries on 4,000 bollywood movies between 1970 and 2017 by ibm and two delhi-based organizations showed that male characters were mentioned nearly twice as many times as their female counterparts. 
sexism was prevalent as female characters are mostly described as “beautiful” and “attractive” whereas men are called “strong” and “successful”. while women go on to marry or love, men were likely to kill or shoot. 
stereotypes or sexist ideas and constructs prevail in the bollywood industry, the item-numbers that shows scan notily clad women surrounded by drunk men drooling over her “spicy” or “theeka” body to an upbeat, irrelevant song. 
when the #metoo movement arrived in the industry, it provided many in the industry and the country in whole hope, hope that justice would be served, hope that this massive evil would be erased. but the movement almost like a soda can fizz at first but then almost instantly died out. 
what happened to the movement? why has no action taken place? why did the buck stop at bollywood?

text:
artifact 5: 
the glitz and the glamour is not the only thing bollywood consists of. 9 out of 10 times, behind every movie, there is a horrifying story of the casting couch. this is even worse for newcomers, people who are trying to find their big break in the industry, men, women anyone who wants to make it big, almost always has to go through this horrendous path. sakshi shivanand captures this casting couch phenomenon in its whole essence by saying “its a professional hazard, you gotta go with it”. within bollywood, it has now become a norm, a quid pro quo situation. people in power exploit the weakers ones, the ones trying to achieve something. they think it’s their right to receive sexual favours from aspiring stars for them to cast them in their movies. big names such as ranveer singh too, have come up and told how even men in the industry are not immune to this. the casting couch culture actually existed in bollywood, a news channel conducted a sting operation. it is visibly clear as shakti kapoor (on whom the operation was conducted) asks for sex in return to a young aspiring actress in order to help her with her career. this clip shows the monstrous world of bollywood which is generally hidden under false fantasies of stardom. the worst part about the casting couch culture is that when smaller, unrecognized players make noise about it, they are either subdued or are crushed. this can be seen in the videos throughout. this is one of the major reasons why people do not want to speak about it, in totality, it is a career suicide. this too can be observed by the actress who spoke out, launched an fir and now is not getting any roles. in a culture which constantly makes people choose certain paths to achieve success, which focuses more on people’s assets rather than their acting skills, it is necessary for big players to come out and speak up about more harsher realities. this is the very reason why actresses such as kalki koechlin have now come out, open in the public and started making people aware of how grave this issue is and how this is the real bollywood under the veil which the public needs to help change.

#metoo #harrasment #bollywood

text:
artifact 4 - tanushree’s dutta’s metoo case
miss tanushree dutta, who had once held the title miss india and has appeared in multiple bollywood can surely be termed an active part of bollywood. however, bollywood owes her another debt. miss dutta helped trigger bollywood’s own metoo movement which gave many women to come to come ahead and speak on harassment that is often concealed in the industry.in september 2018, dutta accused a veteran bollywood actor, nana patekar of trying to sexually harass her during the shoot of a song. she further claimed that she was harassed by goons on refusal. though, nana patekar firmly denied any wrongdoing, te incident gained much popularity. what, however, was found shocking was people’s reaction on the incident. while many did support dutta, many called her names and abused her quite vocally for being an ‘attention seeker’. many called it a publicity stunt and how she was ‘asking for it’, because she had given indecent scenes in her movies. there was also a lot of slutshaming and bodyshaming all over the internet after the incident.it just went to show how indian populace would not back out of abusing someone, to defend their ‘stars’, while some just do not understand the meaning of consent, which is worrying. some people did, however extend their full support to dutta and appealed to people to believe the survivors, this batch also included many popular celebrities. the rest, however, begged off commenting and kept finding excuses to be diplomatic, in typical bollywood fashion.
whatever the verdict be, it cannot be denied that tanushree dutta did bring an issue that was long in waiting into the front. harassment in bollywood has so long suppressed, if the statistics that came forth were anything to believe. this movement gave courage to many- actors and non-actors alike to come and speak on this taboo subject. it also gave a hope to the other fields of india that face harassment to come forth, because everything else that happens in india, bollywood, hopefully, set an example on the youth to come forward if they suffer as such. 
and tanushree dutta is undeniably to be credited for the same.

#metoo #harrasment #bollywood

text:
artifact 3: 
the shant, bhakt baba in the morning and the devil, monster, villain by the name alok nath at night. popular for his roles in several hindi tv shows and blockbuster films. the accusations on the actor only seem to be piling on, and no concrete action has been taken thus far. 
the two cases that headlined several news channels and newspapers after bollywood’s #metoo movement were accusations by two woman in the film industry vinta nanda, sandhya mridul. in sandhya mridul’s facebook post regarding the incident, the tv actress describes the incident in detail. she says that initially, the actor impressed her and that he called her “gods own child” and even openly praised her. she claims that she was a huge fan but thins changed when one night when the crew had gone out to dinner, “babuji” started misbehaving and touching the actress after a few drinks. the actress recalls how that night the actor came to her room and was reluctant to leave, but after latching the actor in the washroom, she was able to get help. but this torture continued, and she recalls the nauseating sensations she had when she’d have to sit on his lap or even touch him during shooting. the calls came. the feeling remained. and when this woman gather the courage to finally speak up about it, what do we do? what happened after the actress spoke up? 
this was only one of the many accusations against the man. several actresses and colleagues claim that the man was almost holy and even a radiant personality during the day but after 6 pm the man became a devil. why then has nothing happened?

there are several questions but very few answers, its bee three months since the incident and no substantial steps have been taken to punish the accused. how do such terrible things go unreported in the industry that we take so much pride in? why do we tolerate such acts? what next? 
the questions are too many but no real answers. was the entire #metoo moment in india a failed build up to nothing? 
something needs to change and soon.

#metoo #harrasment #bollywood #sexualharrasment #castingcouch

the questions are too many but no real answers. was the entire  moment in india a failed build up to nothing? 
something needs to change and soon.

text:
artifact 2: 
sajid khan is famously known for directing mainstream comedy movies in bollywood, gaining major traction for humshakals and housefull. these are the movies that are supposed to spread lighthearted joy for viewers watching with their friends or family and sajid khan has successfully aged to create a name for himself in the genre. but the rising momentum of the #metoo movement taints his rise to fame with allegations of sexual harassment, inappropriate comments and unwelcome sexual advances. incidentally, he is the brother of farah khan and a relative of the akhtar siblings, who have been outrightly progressive about their views and portray that in their work.

these are women who work in spheres that a director associates with everyday. what is appalling is the delusion of power that men on top had over working with them or for them, he stated to saloni chopra, the assistant director and his co worker, that the casting couch was not about one time sexual favours but affairs that are continued even after the job is given to them for them to make sure that they can keep it. he described it as being a “director’s assistant” and not an “assistant director”. he has, on multiple counts, said out crass comments on the sexuality, on how they should behave or wear their clothes and what they should wear or how skinny they should be for him to want to sleep with them. he even flashed his penis to the journalist interviewing him, asking her to compliment him and boasting about his sex life. 
established, respected and reputed bollywood personalities like sajid khan have multiple times over now, like the #metoo movement has shown us, have violated their authority, disrespected women and act on the sense of entitlement that they assume to have. setting precedent and letting the test of time establish clichés. these incidents have indicated, to many, that being associated with progressive celebrities who are known for their opinions to be liberal and progressive, can never be taken for granted as the rest of the family being the same.

text_retweet:
posted @withrepost • @hongjanghyun 더 나은 비주얼을 만드는 것보다 사람이 일을 하며 응당 추구할 수 있는 행복과 권리를 위해서, 용장관스튜디오 전원은 용기를 내어 오늘 용장관의 공식 입장을 발표하고자 합니다.

여러 추측과 소문이 있었지만 용장관은 탁월한 사진가를 배척한 사례가 있습니다. 
해당 사진가는 성적 무절제함과 여성에 대한 반복적인 비도덕적인 행동, 그 밖에도 인간성과 도덕성이 결여된 잦은 사건으로 용장관 뿐만 아니라 그 주변 사람들의 눈과 귀를 의심케 하곤 했었습니다. 
모델들과 부적절한 관계를 가질때에도, 함께 작업을 가장 많이 하고 언제나 그 사진가를 지지해주는 기자에 대해 노골적인 성적 묘사 혹은 성희롱을 할 때에도 주변 사람들은 불편해도 모른척 할 수 밖에 없었습니다. 본인의 사욕을 위한 소비를 하는동안에 어시스턴트의 월급을 수달치 밀려서 퍼스트 어시스턴트가 본인의 통장에서 후배 어시스턴트들의 월급을 주는 일도 일어났습니다. 담배꽁초를 어시스턴트의 얼굴에 던지거나 어시스턴트 부모님의 신용카드로 고가의 의류를 구입하고 빨리 되돌려주지 않았고, 외주 업체들에는 억대의 금액이 밀리도록 결제를 하지 않고 본인의 소비에만 집중했습니다. 혼인 중 기자와 부적절한 관계를 맺을때도 어시스턴트들은 망을 보거나 모르는 척 하고 있을 수 밖에 없었습니다. 
기본적인 인성을 문제로 삼지 않고, 품고 갈 수 있었을지도 모릅니다. 
용장관은 후배를 의미있는 사진가로 양성하는 것뿐만 아니라 나아가 그도 어딘가에서 또 다른 후배들을 끌어줄수 있도록 지식과 경험을 교류하며 어시스턴트와 함께 살아가고 있습니다. 하루중 가족보다 더 긴 시간을, 같은 공간에서 일하며 보내는 사람들에게까지 잘못된 행동을 하는 것은 우리는 더이상 참을 수가 없었습니다. “나한테 언제 대줄거냐” “젖탱이 한 번 만져보자” “어차피 썩을 몸 나한테 한 번 주면 안되겠냐”
“물이 많게 생겼다”

어시스턴트들은 이에 대해 항의를 했다가, 행여 해고되어 오랜 시간 꿈꿔온 사진가가 되지 못할까 두려워하며 보이지 않는 곳에서 소리없이 울고 서로를 보듬으며 버틸 수 밖에 없었습니다.
빈번히 일어나는 언어적, 육체적 성희롱을 그렇게 일년 이상을 참는 것 외에는 방법이 없다고, 쉬쉬 했습니다.

그러던 어느 날 여성 퍼스트 어시스턴트를 차로 불러내서 운전하던 막내 어시스턴트에게는 차에서 내려 망을 보게 하고, 차에서 성폭행과 희롱을 가하는 사건이 발생했습니다. 그러는 동안 남자 어시스턴트들은 코앞에서 누나이자 동료를 지키지 못하는 자괴감과 분노로 눈물을 흘렸습니다. 최악의 사태까지 가는 것은 퍼스트 어시스턴트의 강한 의지로 겨우 막았으나 시간이 지나도 지워지지 않는 큰 충격과 그로 인한 흉터는 당사자에게는 물론, 이 사건을 알고 있던 용장관의 여러 사람들이 마음에 고스란히 남았습니다.

수없이 거절하는 목소리과 두려움에 떠는 목소리, 그리고 무서운 말을 내뱉는 그의 목소리가 담긴 그 날의 녹음 파일을 가지고 여태까지 침묵해 왔습니다.

재기를 위해 “무혐의” 라는 단어로 모든 과오를 일축하고 진정성과 자기반성을 운운하는 것에 저희는 입장을 공식적으로 표명하기로 어려운 결정을 내렸습니다. 수많은 피해자가 자의로 나서지 못하고 있습니다. 피해자가 여성인 성범죄의 대부분이 증거가 무형인 경우가 많은데 무혐의라는 단어를 말하고 그 무게를 받아들이는 데에 주의와 공감을 간곡히 부탁드립니다.

깊이 반성했다고 해서 용서받는 것이 아니며, 용서는 본인이 스스로 하는 것이 아닙니다. 
이 짧은 글에는 다 담지 못하는, 경험과 시간을 공유한 우리는 한 명의 것이 아닌 가족의 상처를 아직도 회복중에 있습니다. 
무혐의란 단어보다 수많은 경험들과 피해에 귀를 기울여 주세요. 우리가 사랑하고 아끼는 모델들, 스탭, 동료들이 오늘 우리의 이 글로 인해 2차적인 피해를 입지 않았으면, 그들의 상처를 진심으로 걱정하며, 용장관은 글을 올립니다. 우리는 그들의 상처가 진짜인지 가짜인지 의심하지 않습니다. 우리는 그들의 고통의 원인은 그들이 아니라는 것을 믿습니다.
#metoo #미투

그러던 어느 날 여성 퍼스트 어시스턴트를 차로 불러내서 운전하던 막내 어시스턴트에게는 차에서 내려 망을 보게 하고, 차에서 성폭행과 희롱을 가하는 사건이 발생했습니다. 그러는 동안 남자 어시스턴트들은 코앞에서 누나이자 동료를 지키지 못하는 자괴감과 분노로 눈물을 흘렸습니다. 최악의 사태까지 가는 것은 퍼스트 어시스턴트의 강한 의지로 겨우 막았으나 시간이 지나도 지워지지 않는 큰 충격과 그로 인한 흉터는 당사자에게는 물론, 이 사건을 알고 있던 용장관의 여러 사람들이 마음에 고스란히 남았습니다.

수없이 거절하는 목소리과 두려움에 떠는 목소리, 그리고 무서운 말을 내뱉는 그의 목소리가 담긴 그 날의 녹음 파일을 가지고 여태까지 침묵해 왔습니다.

재기를 위해 “무혐의” 라는 단어로 모든 과오를 일축하고 진정성과 자기반성을 운운하는 것에 저희는 입장을 공식적으로 표명하기로 어려운 결정을 내렸습니다. 수많은 피해자가 자의로 나서지 못하고 있습니다. 피해자가 여성인 성범죄의 대부분이 증거가 무형인 경우가 많은데 무혐의라는 단어를 말하고 그 무게를 받아들이는 데에 주의와 공감을 간곡히 부탁드립니다.

깊이 반성했다고 해서 용서받는 것이 아니며, 용서는 본인이 스스로 하는 것이 아닙니다. 
이 짧은 글에는 다 담지 못하는, 경험과 시간을 공유한 우리는 한 명의 것이 아닌 가족의 상처를 아직도 회복중에 있습니다. 
무혐의란 단어보다 수많은 경험들과 피해에 귀를 기울여 주세요. 우리가 사랑하고 아끼는 모델들, 스탭, 동료들이 오늘 우리의 이 글로 인해 2차적인 피해를 입지 않았으면, 그들의 상처를 진심으로 걱정하며, 용장관은 글을 올립니다. 우리는 그들의 상처가 진짜인지 가짜인지 의심하지 않습니다. 우리는 그들의 고통의 원인은 그들이 아니라는 것을 믿습니다.
#metoo #미투

사욕을 위한 소비를 하는동안에 어시스턴트의 월급을 수달치 밀려서 퍼스트 어시스턴트가 본인의 통장에서 후배 어시스턴트들의 월급을 주는 일도 일어났습니다 . 담배꽁초를 어시스턴트의 얼굴에 던지거나 어시스턴트 부모님의 신용카드로 고가의 의류를 구입하고 빨리 되돌려주지 않았고 , 외주 업체들에는 억대의 금액이 밀리도록 결제를 하지 않고 본인의 소비에만 집중했습니다 . 혼인 중 기자와 부적절한 관계를 맺을때도 어시스턴트들은 망을 보거나 모르는 척 하고 있을 수 밖에 없었습니다 . 기본적인 인성을 문제로 삼지 않고 , 품고 갈 수 있었을지도 모릅니다 . 용장관은 후배를 의미있는 사진가로 양성하는 것뿐만 아니라 나아가 그도 어딘가에서 또 다른 후배들을 끌어줄수 있도록 지식과 경험을 교류하며 어시스턴트와 함께 살아가고 있습니다 . 하루중 가족보다 더 긴 시간을 , 같은 공간에서 일하며 보내는 사람들에게까지 잘못된 행동을 하는 것은 우리는 더이상 참을 수가 없었습니다 . “ 나한테 언제 대줄거냐 ” “ 젖탱이 한 번 만져보자 ” “ 어차피 썩을 몸 나한테 한 번 주면 안되겠냐 ” “ 물이 많게 생겼다 ” 어시스턴트들은 이에 대해 항의를 했다가 , 행여 해고되어 오랜 시간 꿈꿔온 사진가가 되지 못할까 두려워하며 보이지 않는 곳에서 소리없이 울고 서로를 보듬으며 버틸 수 밖에 없었습니다 . 빈번히 일어나는 언어적 , 육체적 성희롱을 그렇게 일년 이상을 참는 것 외에는 방법이 없다고 , 쉬쉬 했습니다 . 그러던 어느 날 여성 퍼스트 어시스턴트를 차로 불러내서 운전하던 막내 어시스턴트에게는 차에서 내려 망을 보게 하고 , 차에서 성폭행과 희롱을 가하는 사건이 발생했습니다 . 그러는 동안 남자 어시스턴트들은 코앞에서 누나이자 동료를 지키지 못하는 자괴감과 분노로 눈물을 흘렸습니다 . 최악의 사태까지 가는 것은 퍼스트 어시스턴트의 강한 의지로 겨우 막았으나 시간이 지나도 지워지지 않는 큰 충격과 그로 인한 흉터는 당사자에게는 물론 , 이 사건을 알고 있던 용장관의 여러 사람들이 마음에 고스란히 남았습니다 . 수없이 거절하는 목소리과 두려움에 떠는 목소리 , 그리고 무서운 말을 내뱉는 그의 목소리가 담긴 그 날의 녹음 파일을 가지고 여태까지 침묵해 왔습니다 . 재기를 위해 “ 무혐의 ” 라는 단어로 모든 과오를 일축하고 진정성과 자기반성을 운운하는 것에 저희는 입장을 공식적으로 표명하기로 어려운 결정을 내렸습니다 . 수많은 피해자가 자의로 나서지 못하고 있습니다 . 피해자가 여성인 성범죄의 대부분이 증거가 무형인 경우가 많은데 무혐의라는 단어를 말하고 그 무게를 받아들이는 데에 주의와 공감을 간곡히 부탁드립니다 . 깊이 반성했다고 해서 용서받는 것이 아니며 , 용서는 본인이 스스로 하는 것이 아닙니다 . 이 짧은 글에는 다 담지 못하는 , 경험과 시간을 공유한 우리는 한 명의 것이 아닌 가족의 상처를 아직도 회복중에 있습니다 . 무혐의란 단어보다 수많은 경험들과 피해에 귀를 기울여 주세요 . 우리가 사랑하고 아끼는 모델들 , 스탭 , 동료들이 오늘 우리의 이 글로 인해 2차적인 피해를 입지 않았으면 , 그들의 상처를 진심으로 걱정하며 , 용장관은 글을 올립니다 . 우리는 그들의 상처가 진짜인지 가짜인지 의심하지 않습니다 . 우리는 그들의 고통의 원인은 그들이 아니라는 것을 믿습니다 .

text:
.
you were an empty shell of a man.
little did i know you served a purpose.
to awaken my soul,
you had to break down my walls.
you had to be quite alluring.
you reeled me in with your lovely facade,
studied my strengths,
so you could procure them.
and the kinder i was,
the more my weaknesses showed,
and you figured out how you could use them.
you left me in shambles,
with nothing to do,
but look at myself in the face.
my self love was on zero,
you were far from the hero,
you had claimed to represent.
but here i am stronger,
wanting you no longer,
i came out on the other end.
and you are still on your bullshit,
too damaged to admit,
that you are still an empty shell of a man.
💀🖤
.
.

text:
(500) days of summer. (2009)
.
.
love. one of most confusing words in the english language. a person can love another person, a sandwich, a car, a feeling, and a host of other things, people, and places. love. just four letters that mean so much.
.
in marc webb's directorial debut (500) days of summer, we find out exactly what love is. a while ago i saw the trailer for this film and it came with a warning: "this is not a love story. this is a story about love." this could not have been a truer statement.
.
let's face it. we've all done our share of "dumping". whether it's the, "lets just be friends," or the all too familiar, "it's not you, it's me," tactic, as long as you're not on the receiving end it becomes a question of, "how quickly can i get this over with, so i can move on with my life?" equally, all of us (yes even brad pitt) have experienced what it feels like to "be" dumped.
.
there is so much i want to say but can't because it would spoil not just the story but the fun.
.
"(500) days of summer" is clearly a guy's film because it delineates all the joys and sorrows of falling in love from one young man's perspective. .
.
.
.
.
..
.
.
9/10

text:
you may write me down in history
with your bitter, twisted lies,
you may trod me in the very dirt
but still, like dust, i'll rise.

does my sassiness upset you?
why are you beset with gloom?
’cause i walk like i've got oil wells
pumping in my living room.

just like moons and like suns,
with the certainty of tides,
just like hopes springing high,
still i'll rise.

did you want to see me broken?
bowed head and lowered eyes?
shoulders falling down like teardrops,
weakened by my soulful cries?

does my haughtiness offend you?
don't you take it awful hard
’cause i laugh like i've got gold mines
diggin’ in my own backyard.

you may shoot me with your words,
you may cut me with your eyes,
you may kill me with your hatefulness,
but still, like air, i’ll rise.

does my sexiness upset you?
does it come as a surprise
that i dance like i've got diamonds
at the meeting of my thighs?

out of the huts of history’s shame
i rise
up from a past that’s rooted in pain
i rise
i'm a black ocean, leaping and wide,
welling and swelling i bear in the tide.

leaving behind nights of terror and fear
i rise
into a daybreak that’s wondrously clear
i rise
bringing the gifts that my ancestors gave,
i am the dream and the hope of the slave.
i rise
i rise
i rise. #mayaangelou #werise #fearlessgirl #metoo #nadaesperfecto #clandestinacuba #truth #activism #humanrights #faith #truth

text:
where i come from, the biggest celebration isn’t christmas it’s new years. it’s said that however you celebrate your new years, that’s how the whole year will go, which is why it is celebrated with an abundance of food, friends, family, laughter, and joy. last new years i celebrated with israel and although we posted happy photos online, there was a fight that night, i was abused, and i was left crying into my hands.. which is how the rest of the year went until i changed it..
-
attached is the story..
-
-
i didn’t believe that tradition until the hellish start i had to 2018, so now i’d like to do 2019 and do it right. i’ll celebrate it w/ friends, good vibes, love, healthy relationships, laughter, joy, and dancing!! hope everyone celebrates the new year healthy and happy! whether it’s by staying in or going out ❤️

text:
i sit alone in this cafe as every bit of searing pain and guilt comes screaming at me.
—
and for the sixth time since he sent me his email, i read it again. i crave it. i breathe in his words. i love even his subject title, because it’s so him … it’s so me. will anyone else ever write like this to me again?
—
will anyone else hurt me like he did, again?
—
how can he be both my anathema + my panacea?
—
i’m trying so hard to hold back my tears, my uncontrollable internal shakes of escalating hyperventilation, my deepening sense of falling to the rock bottom - as i realize that the only one who gets me is the one who put me here in the first place.
—
🎧where i won’t be found @sevenlions @néonhèart]
—
—
—

text:
b.i.y.b. documentary $3,000 goal

hi! thanks so much for your time and interest, whether you're donating as a birthday gift or just as a friend to my goals.

i'm in the process of directing/filming a documentary based on women of color who suffer from ptsd in the aftermath of toxic and abusive relationships, yet never seek the necessary therapy to recover.
we are burdened with the unfair expectation of making a full recovery under the guise of being strong despite being broken. yet we seldom do recover, without carrying the damage done to us into every future step.
in the film i speak to women from all walks of life who bear their soul, some anonymously, still feeling humiliated from all they endured. 
i visit with therapists who describe in detail, which kind of men, prey on women emotionally and financially to no end. 
the film revolves around my personal experiences and my journey into therapy and finding other women with similar experiences.
the question "why didn't you just leave" has been answered every which way but sensibly. in my film it finally is, its answered truthfully and even scientifically with strength and vulnerability. my goal is to help as many women as possible, by seeing themselves in us and our stories.

if you cannot donate but know someone who can, please share. if you know anyone who can invest and interested in being an executive producer of a project with this subject matter, feel free to have them contact me at jeniciag@gmail.com 
fyi i've covered some great interviews already but more traveling and crew will be needed to finish the project.

thanks again!

text:
good and mad||rebecca traister||⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
•
•
a history of women’s anger and the power it has to make change and drive progress in society.
•
•
i love that traister details not only the rage at men and the world, but also the rage many women have for other women. she doesn’t shy away from the problem with white women and their relationship to white supremacy.
•
•
the book is a truly intersectional text and woc (especially black women) are given proper credit for their work and acknowledged for the erasures along the way. we’re taught about shirley chisholm, barbara lee, maxine waters and it’s fantastic to give them their due.
•
•
it’s not a super easy read, at times is can be slow, but traister balances the history with reflections on her role in the current space with #metoo and the 2016 election etc.
•
•
have you read this? what did you think? how about a favorite feminist book you’ve read?
•
•
full review up on the website, link in bio.
#thestacksreview

text:
end of the story: 
when i was able to grab my phone, i texted my friend because i noticed that he was on his phone, and the other guy didn't notice because he was distracted kissing me again but he was getting too close to my face, too close to my mouth, and that's when i started panicking and send him a text saying "get him away from me please!!". he saw it and rushed next to us saying we had to go or we wouldn't catch the train... i was so relieved... we got out of that place and started walking towards the train station. my friend was always in the middle of us... not because he was doing it on purpose to keep the guy away from me, i was the one keeping my distance... i was having so much fun, and it was awesome because i was dancing and all and i don't usually do that!! for brief moments i was happy.... but he had to ruin it all... on our way to the station i wasn't happy anymore, i wasn't having fun, i felt ashamed, i felt dirty, i felt... sad.... i wasn't ok with what happened, and that guy isn't probably even gonna remember how he ruined my night when he wakes up... 😞😒 and that's the end ma dudes 🤷🏾‍♀️

text_retweet:
wow! just wow! .
this was worth a regram... @stylistmagazine ! .
.
“ ow: in my career what i’ve always tried my best to do, whether on television or through film, is to say something about how men and women really behave. to say how we experience shame, how we love, and how we rage, how we fail, how we retreat, persevere and how we overcome. i’ve interviewed and portrayed people who’ve withstood some of the ugliest things life can throw at you but the one quality all of them seem to share is an ability to maintain hope for a brighter morning even during our darkest nights.
ow: so i want all the girls, watching here now, to know that a new day is on the horizon.  and when that new day finally dawns, it will be because of a lot of magnificent women, many of whom are right here in this room tonight, and some pretty phenomenal men, fighting hard to make sure that they become the leaders who take us to the time when nobody ever has to say, ‘me too’ ever again.” .
.
~ an extract from oprah winfrey’s powerful #metoo speech
.
let change the world together this 2019! .

text:
mina akbari, a seasoned journalist with over twenty years of journalism under her belt has turned her storytelling skills from paper into film for the very first time. mina was born into a well off family impoverished due to an unfortunate economical downturn. because of their hardships she had developed harder skin than the more advantageous youth. at five years old she was in school, by sixteen she had finished high school and entered university to study journalism. she started working early in life determined to succeed. her fearlessness helped her finish projects others were not able to accomplish. so, by her junior year in college she was way ahead of her peers, a paying contributor to her university paper to the point that the professors asked her to do field work in exchange for credit. this powerhouse woman ended up working for over twenty news publications all of which were censored, many of which were shut down, some even before opening, and all of which were replaced by yet another new one. after twenty fruitless years of trying to reach the goal of changing a society, mina was finally tired and retired like many others. she started working out of her home-office and around her fortieth birthday reviewed and assessed her life. as part of that one day when she was flipping through her album she came upon a group photo with her many colleagues in “formerly javanan (youth) square” (a street location and film’s title) and wondered what had happened to all those in that photo and that’s how the story begins and turns into one the best documentary features i have seen in the past decade. the film is setup as a newspaper. each section has a title as if you are flipping through the pages. it is specially pertinent in this era of mistreatment of journalists who are trying to unveil the truth within a global governing political climate, which wants to cover it! mina might be a first time filmmaker but she has done an exquisite job. yet another great female filmmaker whose future works i await with great impatience. bravo! 
#film #filmmaker #documentary #journalism #journalist #oppression #censorship #femalefilmmaker #metoo #filmfestivals #feature #director

text:
written before #metoo, but such a compelling response to it, miriam toews’ women talking is just incredible. hitting all the pain points - some with such brutality that it's hard to keep reading and others with such tenderness. this is the most amazing read about the power of angry and loving women, especially when we're angry, loving, and organized together. .
.
“we are wasting time, pleads greta, by passing this burden, this sack of stones, from one to the next, by pushing our pain away. we mustn't do this. we mustn't play hot potato with our pain. let's absorb it ourselves, each of us, she says. let's inhale it, let's digest it, let's process it into fuel.” .
.
#amreading #readmorewomen #miriamtoews #womentalking

text:
a month has already passed since i left the land downunder. for those that didn't know, i was invited to speak at an event #zafigox in malaysia in early november (amazing experience!) and took the opportunity of being in the region to use my airasia frequent flyer points to get to oz. i had been away since march 2017 😱 it was a whirlwind trip but in that time i was able to share moments with special friends, help my mom get her first smartphone (slowly becoming a pro), spent a few amazing days in byron bay (thank you milton 🙏) and gave a talk at qut (thanks to tamara bird 🙌).
*
that was just the australia part of the trip 😝 i also spent a few days having very productive talks in singapore, ran in vietnam and had a few more days in kuala lumpur to meet other organisations and spend time with some of my new friends from zafigox. quite literally felt like i lived 4 lifetimes in 4 weeks.
*
now back up in europe and settling into what will be a very different, exciting, evolving 2019. more news on that one soon.
biggest hugs
claire 🦋
*
*
*
📷 by my mum on her new iphone 📱

text:
💪超ポジティブになれる映画が遂に公開💕
メーガン・トレイナー「me too」が主題歌！映画『#アイフィールプリティ #人生最高のハプニング』が遂に日本でも公開されました🙌
容姿にコンプレックスを持つ主人公が、ある出来事をきっかけに美女に変身するポジティブな勘違いから巻き起こる騒動を描いたラブコメディ💕😍 主人公・レネー役はアメリカで絶大なる人気を誇るエイミー・シューマーが演じ、日本語吹き替えは人気お笑い芸人の渡辺直美さんが担当！
誰もが共感して、見た後は自分にちょっとだけ自信が持てるようになるハズ😤
映画のサントラも主題歌のメーガン・トレイナーはもちろん、maroon 5、ランチマネー・ルイスなどの楽曲が収録されて絶賛発売中です🎵 .
.

誰もが共感して、見た後は自分にちょっとだけ自信が持てるようになるハズ😤

.

this year is coming to an end and it has been the best year of my life. it wasn’t always easy - but the changes i made and created for myself have made me a better person and turned my life into something i didn’t think was possible.
from leaving the company i built after 10 years with my best friend to checking into rehab to get the help i needed and most importantly meeting the man of my dreams - not to forget all the trips, events, awards, dinners, collaborations and memories - 2018 really delivered! 
looking forward to a new year with lots of love, happiness and maybe a bit of struggle!🌹#bestnine2018

text_retweet:
#repost @goldiiieee137
• • •
"it's changed me forever, but changed doesn't have to mean broken." #ashleyherringblake -
-
book review ⭐⭐⭐⭐
-
in a world where misogyny exists, we need brave women who can turn their scars into stars. we live in a world where the voices of women are dubbed to be insignificant. -
-

this book talks about sensitive topics especially about sexual assault and why women chose to be silent instead of voicing out. because nobody listens when a woman says she's sexually harassed.
-
- "even girls made of stars are captives, bound at the wrists and traded like property. even girls made of stars aren't asked, aren't believed, aren't considered worth the effort unless they can offer something in return.

even girls made of stars buy into those lies sometimes." -
-
in 2006, #metoo movement was started . this movement encourages women to find comfort with each other especially when it comes to sexual harassment. i am a fan of charmed (original) series so the names alyssa milano and rose mcgowan were so familiar to me. the hashtag #metoo went viral last 2017 because alyssa used it to support her friend rose's allegations of sexual harassment against weinstein and the rest is history.

women found their voice. women finally found a way to turn their experiences into something inspiring. but we haven't won the battle yet. if you watch the news, cases of rape and sexual harassments are still rampant. usually, they blame the women for such acts. they would say that if only a woman would not give the perpetrator a reason to do harm to her, this would've never happened. a middle finger to whoever said that. sexual harassment is nobody's fault except the perpetrator himself. 
to all the women who braved their way out into the world and finally accepted to themselves that they are not victims anymore but survivors, my respect is yours. you're the bravest people i know.

#bookreview #girlmadeofstars #goodreads #tbr2018 #2018reads #bookchallenge #sexualassault #metoomovement #rape #feminism #misogyny #womensrights #womenarepeopletoo #mustread #goldiiieee137

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
my life partner and the grounded half of our marriage of visionaries to action, jaimey walking bear has been in the conference marketing business for nearly 15 years, nurturing programs and speakers for spectacular events with @oreillymedia @digitalsummits and more.
.
so when jaimey decided to #dropknowledge on how to make speaking proposals stand out and land gigs for speaking at events, i was stoked he would combine talents of his early days as a radio dj with his heart-centered love of helping people shine through a new podcast.
.
'the audience' is a group of soulful conversations with people creating out loud.
.
http://bit.ly/the-audience-podcast
.
jaimey walking bear—  @bearfuht — hosts speakers, entrepreneurs, and creatives, dishing on their best practices for thriving as public speakers or organizers in the conference / event space. and i’m grateful he shows up as an ally, not afraid to ask the tough questions in how to make conference programs more inclusive and safe for all to enjoy.
.
his first guests made for some hearty soul food as i work toward speaking more frequently again — these creative humans who are part of the launch set include ann handley @annhandley, michael barber @michaeljbarber, melanie deziel @meldeziel, and my coach ajit nawalkha @ajitnawalkha. check out the audience podcast! #theaudiencepodcast
.
.
.
.

text:
#metoo #yotambién #violenciadegénero #maltratopsicológico #machismo
#mispoemas #mam #maríaruizdelapeña 
de la época en la que escribía para no volverme loca. lo hacía de un modo tan esquizoide que, sin querer, le estaba dando toda la información a mi maltratador, algo de lo que no me arrepiento. en febrero se cumplirán tres años del momenti en el que corté las cadenas; aún así, no olvido. "yo te amé, ahora me aterras" 
quiero escapar del miedo pero

el mismo miedo lo impide.

no sé dónde ir para que no me encuentres.

tus palabras se han convertido en ley,

tus abrazos en garras,

tus besos hacen sangrar mis labios.

eres el dueño de mis horas y mis días, 
el señor de mis palabras y mis sueños, 
el propietario de un cuerpo que ya no puede más.

sólo puedo ser tuya, dices tú que me proteges.

sólo puedo mirarte a ti.

sólo puedo hablar contigo, dices tú que eres el único que me entiendes.

juras que me quieres, que sin mí no vives.

prohíbes que salga sola, por temor a perderme

me convences de tu amor, tras cada bofetada.

yo te amé, hace ya mucho, ahora me aterrorizas.

quiero escapar del miedo pero sé 
que no encontraré un lugar donde esconderme.

fotografía de javier a bedrina

text:
инструкция по уходу за бабочками
⠀
✨как кормить бабочку:
1️⃣ наберите стакан воды и разбавьте в ней одну чайную ложку сахара. вода должна быть теплой. налейте сладкую воду в пробку от любой пластиковой бутылки. 
2️⃣ если вы поставите перед бабочкой палец и будете двигать на нее, она сама переползет вам на руку. аккуратно взять бабочку другой рукой, не за крылья, а за брюшко, когда бабочка сидит со сложенными крыльями. 
3️⃣ когда вам удалось правильно взять в руку бабочку, поднесите ее к пробочке, наполненной водой. 
4️⃣ одной рукой вы держите бабочку, другой возьмите зубочистку и с ее помощью размотайте хоботок бабочки, направив его в водичку. 
5️⃣ если бабочка голодна она сразу будет пить. 
6️⃣ когда бабочка напьется, она сама улетит
7️⃣ кормить каждый день, лучше утром.
⠀
✨где держать бабочку:
💠 если у вас в квартире тепло (+20 с и выше) бабочки будут себя нормально чувствовать. будут перелетать со штор на стены, на комнатные растения.
три раза в день их необходимо опрыскивать из цветочного распылителя.
на ночь лучше посадить в коробку. по одной бабочке в одну коробку! в коробку также нужно положить ватку смоченную в воде, чтобы в коробке было влажно.
⠀
✨запахи: 
бабочки чрезвычайно чувствительны к запахам.
яркие и сильные запахи (духи, дезодоранты) могут привлечь бабочку, как, впрочем, и оттолкнуть.
поэтому, если бабочка настойчиво следует за вами – не следует пугаться,  возможно ей просто понравился ваш запах.
⠀
✨локализация: 
сделав несколько кругов по залу, бабочки обычно успокаиваются и рассаживаются на стены, мебель, люстры и т.д.
поскольку бабочки могут сидеть где угодно, в том числе и на полу, чтобы случайно не наступить на бабочек, предупредите ваших гостей о необходимости двигаться аккуратно, смотреть под ноги.
⠀
✨ответственность: 
живая бабочка – существо крайне нежное и уязвимое.
помните, что, приобретая бабочек, вы берёте на себя ответственность за их жизнь.
⠀
👆кормите бабочек и бережно ухаживайте за ними и тогда они будут радовать вас как можно дольше!
name: Живые бабочки🦋Цветы🌺Москва

text:
just saw this and for some reason, it really hit me...i never feel safe walking alone. i don’t even feel safe walking alone in pure daylight, never mind night time! just a few weeks ago i was leaving work and walking to the train when a car with two men stopped me to tell me how good i looked (and then they said some other horrific things) and i was terrified. i truly thought in that moment that i might get kidnapped and die. it makes me so sad and so angry. and now that i think of it, i’m not so sure i ever feel safe. i’m nervous when a man sits next to me on a train or looks in my direction. i’m always extra cautious about who’s following me, and whenever i leave the house my mom reminds me to “be aware of my surroundings”. i’m always on edge. even in the gym, or just anywhere in public where men are around me. how does everyone else feel about this? do you ever feel safe? comment below!! 🎂 by @thesweetfeminist .
.
.

text:
daysjapan編集長だった広河さんからのセクハラ被害のニュース、で2018年が終わる。
2018年、初めての妊娠と出産と、子育てが始まったわたしの人生。
女性、であることをたくさん、考えさせられた１年だった。

韓国ではこの本を読んだとアイドル（red velvet のアイリーンや少女時代のテヨン）が答えただけで炎上したというが、さもありなん。
この本は日本でも受け入れられると思う。
日本ももっと皆が生きやすくなれば良いのにって思う。
薄くて読みやすい。キムジヨンの、その母の、祖母のライフヒストリーが突き刺さる。
この女性たちの苦労は日本も無関係ではない。
来年はもっと女性ということについて考えられる本を読みたいな。

text:
una buena causa…?
www.eltranviadelamoda.com 
las buenas causas empiezan siendo buenas… y luego acaban siendo linchamientos.

como las acusaciones en el movimiento #metoo : denunciar es una buena causa.
como en los abusos sexuales de los curas: denunciar es una buena causa.
como en las ong en países subdesarrollados: denunciar es una buena causa.
como en el abuso de poder de los políticos: denunciar es una buena causa.
como la violencia de genero: denunciar es una buena causa.

pero…qué ocurre cuando se denuncian abusos sexuales falsos?
y con las familias que siguen llevando a sus hijos a colegios católicos?
y con las personas que siguen pagando una cuota al mes a una ong creyendo que hacen algo bueno en el mundo?
y con los que confían en los políticos?
y con las que denuncian malos tratos cuando no han existido? 
todo esto…existe. nadie a sus solas se engaña.

las buenas causas son necesarias y son buenas…pero tienen que ser demostrables una a una, como las malas. hoy en día todo tiene que ser demostrado.
generalizar no es posible porque acaban pagando justos…por pecadores.
linchamientos a personas totalmente inocentes. 
durante una etapa de mi vida tuve una suegra terriblemente maligna y como tal…asi lo está pagando ahora abandonada, por aquellos hijos en los que confío y que por supuesto…le engañaron. 
pero les puedo jurar que conozco a suegras maravillosas, amables y queredoras y que una excepción como la mia no hace la regla. así aprendi que no se puede generalizar.

las buenas causas siempre empiezan siendo buenas y luego las excepciones tergiversadas y tóxicas son las que hacen la noticia. 
porque lo malo...siempre vende.

denunciar sí, siempre que sea verdad y por favor por una buena causa. para eso...apoyo total!!!

text:
[kilas balik 16 film festival bali 2018]

6 desember 2018.

pada hari kelima, pemutaran program film pendek dan sesi #hearmetoo dilakukan di warung men brayut (@menbrayut) pukul 16:00 wita.

kegiatan diawali dengan #hearmetoo session dengan tema "mengenal kekerasan berbasis gender dalam konteks psikologis" bersama i putu galang dharma putra s., m.psi., psikolog (@balisoulsociety) dan dilanjutkan dengan pemutaran program film berjudul "untold"; berisi lima film pendek, yaitu har, perfect p, marriage matrix, anak lanang, dan muslimah. program film pendek ini dikurasi oleh rickdy vanduwin (@shutuprick).
.
@gshrudayana @kisara_bali @lbh_bali

[kilas balik 16 film festival bali 2018]

8 desember 2018.

pada hari keenam, kegiatan kembali dilakukan di warung men brayut (@menbrayut) pukul 16:00 wita.

kegiatan diawali dengan pemutaran film "the mirror never lies" (2011) karya kamila andini. setelah pemutaran, kegiatan dilanjutkan dengan #hearmetoo session dengan tema "fashion dan lingkungan" bersama myra juliarti (desainer @akusiji) dan dian suri (desainer @kunangjewelry).
